                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1414: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 8, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Supplementing my telegram No. 34, April 7, 11 a.m. Since Zúñiga and myself
                    are agreed upon the advisability of an early meeting <pb facs="0166" n="158"
                        xml:id="pg_158"/> of the Commission I have asked Ocheltree to suggest to the
                    President of Commission that he send a (not categorical) letter or telegram to
                    Dr. Rodríguez apprising him of our feeling and asking what would be the earliest
                    date that he could join us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
